'''Alexander Killen Macbeth''' CMG, DSc, FAA (1889–1957), generally called Killen or A. Killen Macbeth, was an Irish born academic and organic chemist who from 1928 until his retirement in 1954 was the [[Angas Professor of Chemistry]] at the [[University of Adelaide]]. In 1946 he was appointed a [[Companion of the Order of St Michael and St George]], and in 1955 he was elected [[Fellow of the Australian Academy of Science]].<ref name=FAA> {{cite web |url=https://www.science.org.au/fellowship/fellows/alexander-killen-macbeth-cmg-dsc-faa |title= Alexander Killen Macbeth, CMG, DSc, FAA |publisher= www.science.org.au }}</ref><ref name=AAS> {{cite web |title= Alexander Killen Macbeth 1889-1957 |work= Biographical memoirs |publisher= Australian Academy of Science |url= https://www.science.org.au/files/userfiles/fellowship/memoirs/documents/macbeth.pdf }}</ref><ref name=trove> {{cite web |url= http://trove.nla.gov.au/people/1476132?c=people |title= Macbeth, Alexander Killen, FAA (1889-1957)] |publisher= trove.nla.gov.au }}</ref><ref name=eoas> {{cite web |title= Macbeth, Alexander Killen (1889 - 1957) |work= Biographical entry |publisher= Encyclopaedia of Australian Science |url= http://www.eoas.info/biogs/P000587b.htm }}</ref><ref name=CMG> {{cite web |title= The Order of St Michael and St George - Companion |date= 1 January 1946 |quote= For public services |url= http://www.itsanhonour.gov.au/honours/honour_roll/search.cfm?aus_award_id=1066368&search_type=simple&showInd=true }}</ref><ref> {{cite web |url= https://physsci.adelaide.edu.au/about/chemistry/history/angas-chair/ |title= Angas Chair of Chemistry |publisher= University of Adelaide }}</ref>
