'''Chapais''' is a crater on [[Mars]], named after the community of [[Chapais, Quebec]], Canada.  Chapais Crater is located at 22.6° south latitude, and 20.6° west longitude.  Its diameter is {{convert|37.4|km|mi|1}}.

Its name was adopted in 1976 by the [[International Astronomical Union]]'s Working Group for Planetary System Nomenclature (IAU/WGPSN).

