'''Inuvik''' is an [[Impact crater]] located outside the perennial north [[Martian polar ice caps|polar cap]] on [[Mars]].<ref>M. Thueson and H. Xie, [http://www.utsa.edu/lrsg/Paper/2355.pdf "Water Ice Investigation in Crater of Residual Polar Region using THEMIS Data"], Lunar and Planetary Science XXXVIII (2007)</ref> The crater's diameter is 20.5 kilometres, and it lies at latitude 78.7°N, longitude 28.6°W.  In 1988, the [[International Astronomical Union|IAU]]'s [[Working Group for Planetary System Nomenclature]] (WGPSN) named the crater after the town of [[Inuvik, Northwest Territories]], Canada.

