{{infobox television | | show_name = Lewis & Clark: Great Journey West | image =<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Lewis & Clark Great Journey West DVD.jpg|thumb|Caption text]] --> | caption = | picture_format = | runtime = 40 minutes | creator = | narrated = Jeff Bridges | country = USA | network = | first_aired = | last_aired = | num_episodes = 1 | website = http://www.nationalgeographic.com/lewisandclark/movie.html }}
'''''Lewis & Clark: Great Journey West''''' is a 40-minute documentary film released by National Geographic, produced by "Simon and Goodman Picture Company", recapping the [[Lewis and Clark Expedition]]. It was first released in theaters across the country on May 1, 2002 and was last shown in theaters May 28, 2007 before being released on VHS and DVD.<ref>http://www.nationalgeographic.com/lewisandclark/theaters.html</ref>
Actors recreate the experiences of [[Meriwether Lewis]], [[William Clark (explorer)|William Clark]] and [[Sacagawea]] ([[Alex Rice]]) on the "Corps of Discovery Expedition" (1804–1806) as they make the first crossing of what would later become the United States. The film is narrated by [[Jeff Bridges]].
