[[File:Arnoldi-127.jpg|thumb|Vladimir Mitrofanovich Arnoldi]]
'''Vladimir Mitrofanovich Arnoldi''' ({{lang-ru|Влади́мир Митрофа́нович Арно́льди}}) ([[Kozlov]] (Michurinsk), [[Russia]] (1871–1924)) was a [[Russia]]n professor of [[biology]]. He was a Corresponding Member of [[Russian Academy of Sciences]] and scientifically listed a number of valuable plants of [[Malaysia]].

He lived in the Russian city of [[Tambov]] for much of his life. His son [[Constantin Arnoldi]] became a prominent [[entomologist]].

